{# AFFiNE merges this file over its built-in defaults at startup (it reads
   ~/.affine/config/config.json, which is this app's config bind mount). The admin panel
   writes the same settings to the database and would override this, so configure OIDC
   here and leave the panel's OAuth section alone.

   `providers.oidc` is deliberately one flattened key rather than nested providers -> oidc:
   that is the key AFFiNE registers its config descriptor under, and it is what the override
   merge matches on to replace the value wholesale.

   `args.scope` is set explicitly because AFFiNE omits the scope parameter entirely when it
   is unset (upstream issue #8752), and Authelia rejects the request without it. It must stay
   in sync with the `affine` client's scopes in deploys/docker_vm/proxies/vars.py.

   The default claim mapping (sub / email / name) already matches Authelia's userinfo
   response, so no claim_* overrides are needed.

   auth: both default to true, so allowSignup must be turned off explicitly -- otherwise
   anyone who can reach the app on the LAN can register themselves an account by email.
   The two flags are separate gates and both are load-bearing: allowSignup=false blocks
   self-registration via email/magic-link (auth controller), while allowSignupForOauth=true
   keeps Authelia SSO able to create accounts on first login (oauth controller). Setting
   the latter to false would lock out every new user, SSO included. -#}
{
  "auth": {
    "allowSignup": false,
    "allowSignupForOauth": true
  },
  "oauth": {
    "providers.oidc": {
      "issuer": "https://auth.[[ host.data.domain ]]",
      "clientId": "affine",
      "clientSecret": "[[ affine_oidc_client_secret ]]",
      "args": {
        "scope": "openid profile email"
      }
    }
  }
}
